\newcommand{\labscript}[2]{\textsf{#1} --- \emph{#2}} % this line defines a new command called "\labscript", and the "[2]" means your command takes two arguments "#1" and "#2". The final bracketed expression is the code that will execute when you call your command, with the relevant argument in the relevant position. This is used here to allow you to reference the GP32 laboratory manuscript using our "house style" formatting. Argument #1 is the code, GP32 in this case, and argument #2 is the title, in this case "Latent heat of vaporisation of nitrogen".

